# RallyApp — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- React Native 0.83 (bare workflow) + Expo SDK 55
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + PostGIS + Auth + Realtime)
- expo-location (NOT @react-native-community/geolocation)
- @react-native-firebase/messaging (lazy-loaded — do NOT move init to top level)
- React Navigation: native-stack + bottom-tabs

## Run commands
- `npm run ios` / `npm run android` — local dev build
- `npm start` — Metro bundler (separate terminal)
- `npm test` — jest
- `npm run lint` — eslint
- EAS cloud builds: `npm run eas:build:dev:ios` / `eas:build:dev:android`

## Architecture rules

### Service layer — enforce strictly
All Supabase calls go through `src/services/`. NEVER query Supabase directly from components.
- activityService.ts — create/fetch/join activities
- userService.ts — profile CRUD, device tokens
- locationService.ts — permissions, position, background
- chatService.ts — threads, messages, unread counts
- friendsService.ts — friend requests, listing
- notificationService.ts — Firebase push tokens, handlers
- reviewService.ts — post-match reviews

Supabase client: `src/services/api/supabase.ts` (has custom fetch for trailing-slash URL bug + AsyncStorage session).

### Env vars
- Never hardcode keys. All env vars via `src/constants/config.ts` (uses react-native-config).
- Copy `.env.example` → `.env`. EAS secrets mirror the same var names.

### Platform differences — critical
- Android: NO `watchPosition`. Use `getCurrentPositionAsync` + `getLastKnownPositionAsync` fallback.
- Android 13+: runtime notification permission required.
- iOS vs Android have different Firebase cold-start timing — Firebase is lazy-loaded intentionally.

### Error handling
- Always wrap service calls in try-catch using the `debugIngest` utility (`src/utils/debugIngest.ts`).
- `DevLocationLogPanel` and `debugIngest` are intentional debug infrastructure — do NOT remove.

### Performance
- Use `React.memo` for list items in ActivityDetail and ChatList.

## Key features
- **Flexible Activity Mode**: host sets constraints → participants submit time/location preferences → system auto-finalizes
- **Anonymous-Until-Confirmed**: identity hidden until host approves; friends always see real identity
- **Deep Link Auth**: `rallyapp://auth/callback` handles Supabase magic links
- **Profile Auto-Create**: AuthContext creates profile on first auth if missing

## Navigation (`src/navigation/AppNavigator.tsx`)
- Auth Stack: Login → Signup
- Main Stack: Bottom tabs (Home/Map/Friends/Profile) + modals (ActivityDetail, CreateActivity, ChatList, ChatThread)

## Design
- Styling: `StyleSheet.create` preferred. Follow `src/constants/theme.ts` for colors/spacing.
- Do not create new base components if `src/components/` has a suitable one.

## Task tracking
- Open tasks: `docs/TASKS.md` — work one task at a time
- Release blockers are at the top of that file — fix in order: Data correctness → Privacy → Crashes → UX
